    Class Description
    AbstractAlgorithm<ST,​PT>
    Abstract implementation of Algorithm containing fields common to all algorithms
    AbstractChoice<O>
    Base class for all choices taking care of the generic features
    Algorithm<ST,​PT>
    Interface for machine learning algorithm that solves a problem It is based on the concept of Problem and Solution spaces, where one or more Problem Genomes PT can be transformed into one or more Solution Genomes GT
    Analytics
    Analytics tool for an Algorithm
    Cachet
    Partial Quality of a Solution.
    CachetEvaluator<GT,​PT>
    A CachetEvaluator determines a single quality characteristic on a Solution and will be used by the Evaluator.
    Choice<O>
    Interface all choices must implement
    Configurable
    Defines generic configuration options for classes in Machinelearning
    ConfigurableChoice<O extends Configurable>
    Helper class for experiment.
    Descriptor<T>
    Contains data for the options of algorithms.
    Evaluator<ST,​PT>
    Evaluates the quality of a Solution according to a fitness function The fitness function consists of several cachets that are summed up
    Experiment<ST,​PT>
    Class for conducting machinelearning experiments.
    ExperimentGroup<ST,​PT>
    Class for conducting machinelearning experiments.
    ExperimentIdentifier
    Identifier encapsulation for a specific experiment
    ExperimentResult<ST,​PT>

    FixedChoice<O>
    Contains a choice to be statically injected.
    Gene<T>

    ListDescriptor<T>

    MinMaxDescriptor<T>
    Used for defining primitive settings.
    NToOneSolutionCreator<ST,​PT>
    Solution Creator that produces a n:1 mapping of ST to PT by using GeneCreator.
    OneToOneSolutionCreator<ST,​PT>
    Generic solution creator that produces a 1:1 mapping of ST to PT by using GeneCreator
    Problem<PT>
    Describes a machine learning problem that needs to be solved A problem consists of genes that are the minimal building blocks of a problem.
    ProblemChoice<O>
    Helper class for experiment.
    ProblemGene<PT>
    Specific Implementation of the Gene Class representing a Genome in a machinelearning Problem
    RandomUtil
    This random util should be used in every class needing to create random values, as we can force the seed centrally.
    SingleChoiceConfig<O>
    Helper class for experiment.
    SingleUnwrappingChoice<O>
    Helper class for experiment.
    Solution<ST,​PT>
